    "Indeed, conventional understanding suggests that LLMs generally show consistent performance improvements with increased scale.",
    "However, contrary to this expectation, there are instances where this trend is reversed, indicating that mere augmentation of model scale does not necessarily translate to improved task performance.",
    "This phenomenon, illustrated in [31], underscores the importance of various factors such as training objectives and data quality in optimizing the performance of LLMs.",
    "Unfortunately, our experiments with the LLaMA2-7B model did not yield favorable outcomes (the accuracy is reported in the last two rows of Table 4), highlighting the complexity of optimizing LLM performance within the BPLLM pipeline.Continuing our examination of the results, we delved into the potential effects of enlarging the knowledge base within the vector database by incorporating multiple process models to provide to the LLM.",
    "Our investigation considered both process models having similar and different activities and objectives to assess the performance implications on the BPLLM pipeline.Initially, we examined the impact of integrating two distinct business processes, namely the previously introduced Food Delivery and Reimbursement process models, into the knowledge base."
